  <!-- Edge Insights: FPU Bug -->
  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>Edge Insight: FPU Hardware Issues.</h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="80">
    During physical testing, the SVM model was disqualified due to catastrophic floating-point
    precision errors on the ESP32 FPU, where precision loss in the
    <code class="inline-code">expf()</code> instruction inverted valid decision boundaries.
    This underscores the critical urgency of <strong style="color:#211f1a;">validating
    benchmarks on the final hardware rather than relying solely on analytical simulations.</strong>
  </p>

